summary:
[[MORE]] Taylor wrote this song for Jon and Daenerys.  I will not hear otherwise. 

Knew he was a killer first time that I saw...
caption:
Taylor wrote this song for Jon and Daenerys.  I will not hear otherwise.

Knew he was a killer first time that I saw him
Wonder how many girls he had loved and left haunted
But if he’s a ghost, then I can be a phantom
Holdin’ him for ransom


I mean….Hello?

Continuing….

Some, some boys are tryin’ too hard
He don’t try at all, though
Younger than my exes but he act like such a man, so
I see nothing better, I keep him forever
Like a vendetta-ta


“I’m a prisoner on this island.”

He doesn’t even look back. He wants to, of course, but he doesn’t.  What a boss. And the exes?

I’ll take those damn puppy heart eyes any day.

Moving on.

I-I-I see how this is gon’ go
Touch me and you’ll never be alone
I-Island breeze and lights down low
No one has to know

(Except everyone will know because they be making all that noise during their boat sex, but anyway)

Me, I was a robber first time that he saw me
Stealing hearts and running off and never saying sorry

(Bye-bye, Daario)


But if I’m a thief, then he can join the heist
And we’ll move to an island-and

(They have their own fucking island that already fucking belongs to them)

And he can be my jailer, Burton to this Taylor
Every lover known in comparison is a failure
I forget their names now, I’m so very tame now
Never be the same now, now

(Drogo raped her ever night for awhile. I’ve settled it that Daario isn’t all that great in bed. But I don’t think she’s tamed.  If anything, Jon is in for some things he never imagined. Thanks, Doreah)

In the middle of the night, in my dreams
You should see the things we do, baby
In the middle of the night in my dreams
I know I’m gonna be with you
So I take my time
Are you ready for it?
Ooh, are you ready for it?

(Oh Dany, I can only imagine the things you’re imagining doing to that boy)

Baby, let the games begin
Let the games begin
Let the games begin
Baby, let the games begin
Let the games begin
Let the games begin

I mean….she ain’t talkin’ about the Game of Thrones.

Thank you, Taylor Swift, for your full-throated endorsement of Jonerys.

summary: Is it fair to say Sansa and Catelyn were the outsiders in the Stark family? Ned, Jon, Robb, Arya and Bran all seemed to have an...
question: Is it fair to say Sansa and Catelyn were the outsiders in the Stark family? Ned, Jon, Robb, Arya and Bran all seemed to have an idyllic dynamic with these two bringing all the conflict (Catelyn made Jon’s life living hell and Sansa bullied Arya). Rickon doesn’t seem to really factor in.
answer:
No, I do not think this is a fair or accurate representation of Stark family dynamics. Due to the accepted norms and power dynamics of their society, it’s Jon and Arya who were the (relative) outsiders, not Catelyn or Sansa. Jon is a bastard, Arya does not fit her assigned gender norms. By contrast, Catelyn is the respected Lady of Winterfell, secure in her relationships with her husband, her children, and the castle staff, while Sansa is exactly what a young noble girl is expected to be. They’re the insiders.

It’s also clear from both sisters that despite their AGoT conflict and a certain amount of tension, Sansa and Arya love each other. Arya’s and Jon’s outsider status did not preclude them having positive, loving relationships with other members of their family, as well as with each other.

summary: Gendry: Hey, you know what's weird? After me and Arya get married, when you introduce me to people, you're gonna have to say,...
body:
Gendry: Hey, you know what’s weird? After me and Arya get married, when you introduce me to people, you’re gonna have to say, “This is my brother-in-law Gendry.” Not, “my friend Gendry”. “Brother-in-law Gendry.” That’s weird, isn’t it?

Jon: Couldn’t I just say, “This is Gendry?”

Gendry: …sure, do whatever what you want.
